<subSubSection id="B03A06358D2E55377596DD78D5C4597D" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="83D8D4FD700A7B81B0C41EA3357A8AF4" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A5AF106E1583041F219A8118E41A1558" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">
Differs from 
<taxonomicName id="18D29AF01DE9B2AB360997D4E35F2B7E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Columnea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Columnea picta" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="picta">
<emphasis id="826C16052DB73EDA0ECE8E4BFF9F4904" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Columnea picta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a nearly tubular corolla (vs. deeply bilabiate corolla) that is equal to or shorter than the calyx lobes (vs. corolla that extends beyond the calyx lobes).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
