<subSubSection id="8DF18DE5478214B67B0B0E5948A04FEB" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" type="description">
<paragraph id="10822488582235E43DFEB101EE6E46D1" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FF30DF196D4A2276304DC52544D436D4" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">
Facultative epiphyte with dorsiventral shoots to 1.5 m long, subwoody, suffrutescent, glabrescent below, sparsely pilose above; internodes 5-10 cm near base, then clustered at branch apex. Leaves opposite, strongly anisophyllous, papyraceous when dry; larger leaf nearly sessile, petioles succulent, 0.3-0.8 cm long, glabrous; blade asymmetric, broadly oblanceolate, 7-30 
<normalizedToken id="3AB0C5B9CB5D47EEF50244C96BD88FE9" originalValue="Ã">x</normalizedToken>
3-6.6 cm, base oblique, apex acuminate, margin serrate, adaxially uniformly green with bright red apex, glabrous, abaxially light green with bright red apex, sparsely pilose along the venation, lateral veins 7-14, primary vein bright red, secondary veins red at base and green adaxially; smaller leaf sessile and often clasping the base of the stem; blade asymmetric, lanceolate 0.5-1.5 
<normalizedToken id="A9974DD50682FFCE60705611E13BC13F" originalValue="Ã">x</normalizedToken>
0.4-0.5 cm, base oblique, apex acuminate, margin serrate, green with red apex on both sides, adaxially glabrous, abaxially sparsely pilose. Inflorescence reduced, appearing in clusters of 1-4 axially flowers; peduncles absent or highly reduced (&lt;0.2 cm long); bracts 1-2, light green, oblanceolate, 0.7-1 
<normalizedToken id="D0B921A3580C656F621AAF431C564122" originalValue="Ã">x</normalizedToken>
0.2-0.3 cm, glabrous on both sides. Flowers subtended by elongate pedicels, 1.5-2.4 cm long, sparsely pilose, with enations near the apex; calyx lobes 5, nearly free, mostly equal in size and shape, dorsal lobe slightly smaller, 1.5-2.3 
<normalizedToken id="92C0E87C54C4CE2DFE21F2E7BB940228" originalValue="Ã">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 cm, ovate, apex acute, margin serrate, yellow with red splotches in the center, inner and outer surfaces sparsely pilose; corolla tubular and erect, 1-1.9 cm long, outer and inner surfaces pilose, limb shallowly bilabiate, mostly yellow with red striations on lateral and ventral lobes, corolla lobes 0.2-0.5 
<normalizedToken id="3DD48D6D72CA5692AAE8341272526A5D" originalValue="Ã">x</normalizedToken>
0.2-0.4 cm. Androecium of 4 stamens, filaments connate at the base for 0.1-0.3 cm and forming a filament curtain, free portion of filaments ca. 1.5 cm long, glabrous; anthers longer than broad, ca. 2 
<normalizedToken id="78ED8E45931F2A7CB71DFCAC6FDC3E79" originalValue="Ã">x</normalizedToken>
1.5 mm, dehiscing by longitudinal slits; staminode absent; nectary a bilobed dorsal gland, glabrous; ovary superior, densely pilose, 0.2-0.4 
<normalizedToken id="D54894AAC8B7B1DA5C6AEF51378C133A" originalValue="Ã">x</normalizedToken>
0.2 cm, style ca. 1.4 cm long, glabrous, stigma included and shallowly bifid. Fruit an indehiscent oblong white berry, 1.2 
<normalizedToken id="83A16F9DBD6A50E53477E6B5BD8EB870" originalValue="Ã">x</normalizedToken>
0.72 cm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B7055794B79CBC84A2092D3F54DB9231" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" type="phenology">
<paragraph id="A462D4A6759F2613808FE7FECDF6E48B" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="280F224795CED1AA40C73F38D2B8B75C" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">This species was documented with flowers in June and May. Fruits have been recorded in June.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="88E1CC08CC2A0E9BF5827511DBADD6C5" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="0F94157A4990760AC58B776831C0802A" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D8767E4EFB7C90C6076066BA7DDCEB85" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName id="DD09F8F5BAEB296962A16AF12FC42F5F" authorityName="J. L. Clark &amp; Clavijo" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Columnea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Columnea tecta" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tecta">Columnea tecta</taxonomicName>
refers to the 
<normalizedToken id="5AD134F60D4F9E0B1811F9D8D7EE3874" originalValue="âhiddenâ">&quot;hidden&quot;</normalizedToken>
or relatively short corolla tube that does not exceed the length of the calyx lobes, an unusual character in 
<taxonomicName id="F9D1DDB7E238D0970D6B02DEBE703E61" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Columnea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Columnea" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B64C07758C87DCB193ABF4466306E06E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Columnea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="691F09887C715BEA745DF952D0C23349" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="ED4F2C5FA8C6D8750E84F19996CDA64F" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Distribution and preliminary assessment of conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3F38909A23A6EF0D1D22FD9A942350A7" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">
This species has not been found in any formally protected areas. According to the IUCN Red List criteria (
<bibRefCitation id="8C9128AF219392456944F35BB5D89962" author="IUCN [Species Survival Commission]" journalOrPublisher="Rheedea" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" refId="B4" refString="IUCN [Species Survival Commission], 2001. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. IUCN, Gland and Cambridge." title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. IUCN, Gland and Cambridge." year="2001">IUCN 2001</bibRefCitation>
) for limited geographic range (B2a, less than five locations) and considering the uncertain future of habitat conservation of western Andean forests, 
<taxonomicName id="303215D491A982DF640F976871235DB2" authorityName="J. L. Clark &amp; Clavijo" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Columnea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Columnea tecta" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tecta">
<emphasis id="514FD1539A89491E15BD31B54AB81A50" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Columnea tecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be listed in the category Endangered (EN).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="201302E053701CB6D2A34F4141C50650" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" type="comments">
<paragraph id="3DF4FAFB0FDFF149DA9D9B97998207AB" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="15EC4128262C4011F11964C02314BC9E" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">
<taxonomicName id="5567D827957FD35423AB3B4F0F321B03" authorityName="J. L. Clark &amp; Clavijo" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Columnea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Columnea tecta" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tecta">
<emphasis id="4C3D89233A4FF6AF7DA55BA111C7C409" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Columnea tecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is readily distinguished from all other congeners by relatively short corollas that barely exceed the length of the calyx lobes (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="83DDEE928794D5551071D9B60A5D7D21" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Columnea tecta J. L. Clark &amp; Clavijo A mature flower with lateral calyx lobe pulled back B Oblong white berry C mature flower D dorsiventral habit (A-D from J. L. Clark et al. 13433). Photos by J. L. Clark." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.182.69016.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/590855" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">7</figureCitation>
). The corollas of 
<taxonomicName id="48A0DAE9ED1831F120BE4C918C9C079A" authorityName="J. L. Clark &amp; Clavijo" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Columnea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Columnea tecta" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tecta">
<emphasis id="E900EB401863C130E244150577E23C4A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Columnea tecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have limbs that are shallowly bilabiate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="980C9E06D5AD143E7092389ADC0248F0" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Columnea tecta J. L. Clark &amp; Clavijo A mature flower with lateral calyx lobe pulled back B Oblong white berry C mature flower D dorsiventral habit (A-D from J. L. Clark et al. 13433). Photos by J. L. Clark." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.182.69016.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/590855" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">7A</figureCitation>
) in contrast to the deeply bilabiate corollas of 
<taxonomicName id="9395F5761885895100ADE2E89957D5D3" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Columnea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Columnea picta" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="picta">
<emphasis id="901BA280E40A8F806E0E6E751A7CB3C4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Columnea picta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6898761CE2D17F89952086E2C592DFFF" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Columnea picta H. Karst A lateral view of flower featuring deeply bilobed corolla B ventral view of flower during anthesis C mature flower featuring curled lower lobe D dorsiventral habit (A, B from J. L. Clark &amp; L. Jost 16301 C from J. L. Clark et al. 15393 D from J. L. Clark, M. Mailloux &amp; S. Seger 7942). Photos by J. L. Clark." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.182.69016.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/590854" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">6A</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="7F24F53D3E0C8A0914BCBD0CE9445B22" authorityName="J. L. Clark &amp; Clavijo" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Columnea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Columnea tecta" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tecta">
<emphasis id="5917A8117E40EF1B6DC74B04B75ED80E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Columnea tecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="ECA0D2E6B8B7AA084328D9518011D029" genus="C." lsidName="C. picta" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="picta">
<emphasis id="5CF31136FF850B7EACD3885B0FB4FAD3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">C. picta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are vegetatively similar by the presence of a dorsiventral habit with red apices on both leaf surfaces. The corolla tubes of 
<taxonomicName id="3AD13B188DEB2D85474CE87739428A18" genus="C." lsidName="C. tecta" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="tecta">
<emphasis id="48CBA7E3487B75436C6B82E1671532D5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">C. tecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are short (less than the length of the calyx lobes and shallowly bilabiate) relative to the longer corolla tubes of 
<taxonomicName id="59847875C9172BCC81A101A956E7661E" genus="C." lsidName="C. picta" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="picta">
<emphasis id="110300E9CC20BD91D4BCE1FC608CDD20" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">C. picta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(exceeding the length of the calyx lobes and deeply bilabiate). 
<taxonomicName id="70C31F976CBD682006D1F1B45F0588A6" authorityName="J. L. Clark &amp; Clavijo" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Columnea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Columnea tecta" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tecta">
<emphasis id="A401BA073A5EE18FA8DF4F39029D6166" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Columnea tecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="5F56B87169CA4BA7445ADFFFF603CBE5" genus="C." lsidName="C. angulata" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="angulata">
<emphasis id="6277FA046716D919C13D9E0CBD80C146" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">C. angulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a straight orientation of the corolla relative to the calyx (vs. oblique to perpendicular in 
<taxonomicName id="A2481CA3A7E21C549E2BF886DA203B63" genus="C." lsidName="C. angulata" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" rank="species" species="angulata">
<emphasis id="E09B05C5223CC2605EF55888724C9499" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">C. angulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
